OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Thu 9 Jul to Sat 18 Jul
OL,6,FHigh pressure will continue to prevail
OL,7,Facross England and Wales, likely
OL,8,Fextending its influence into the
OL,9,Fnorthern UK for a time. This will
OL,10,Fcontinue to bring dry and very warm
OL,11,Fweather across England and Wales, but
OL,12,Fthere is an outside chance of the odd
OL,13,Flocalised thunderstorms at times. High
OL,14,Fpressure may extend northwards to
OL,15,Fbring periods of drier and warmer
OL,16,Fweather to most of Scotland and
OL,17,FNorthern Ireland too. Winds will be
OL,18,Flight to moderate for most.
OL,19,FTemperatures will be widely very warm
OL,20,Fat first, although not as hot nor
OL,21,Fhumid as seen in June. There are
OL,22,Fsignals for the heatwave to ease back
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Fto more normal summer temperatures in
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,Fthe week commencing Monday 13 July.
